2500|$|Las Casas and Angulo founded Rabinal, and {{the city}} of <b>Cobán</b> {{was the center of the}} new Catholic doctrine. A few years later, the natives started {{settling}} following the Spanish model and several towns were settled, like Tactic. The name [...] "War zone" [...] was change for [...] "Vera Paz" [...] (true peace), name that became official in 1547. <b>Cobán</b> received the title of an imperial city by Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor and in 1599 <b>Cobán</b> became bishop's see. It was briefly known during this period as Ciudad Imperial (Spanish for [...] "Imperial City") in Charles's honor.|$|E
