2500|$|The Northern Transversal Strip {{was officially}} created during the {{government}} of General Carlos Arana Osorio in 1970, by Decree 60-70 in the Congress, for agricultural development. [...] The area included within the municipalities: San Ana Huista, San Antonio Huista, Nentón, Jacaltenango, San Mateo Ixtatán, and Santa Cruz Barillas in Huehuetenango; Chajul and San Miguel Uspantán in Quiché; <b>Cobán,</b> Chisec, San Pedro Carchá, Lanquín, Senahú, Cahabón and Chahal, in Alta Verapaz and the entire department of Izabal.|$|E
